---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Luxembourg Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/luxembourg/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Belgium for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/belgium' },
  { title: 'Germany for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/germany' },
  { title: 'France for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/france' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'luxFit', header: 'Luxembourg Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€420-590/mo', luxFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€490-690/mo', luxFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€380-540/mo', luxFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€360-520/mo', luxFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Luxembourg CNS', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'N/A', monthlyFrom: '~5.6% income', luxFit: 'For Residents' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '€380-590', annual: '€4,560-7,080' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '€520-780', annual: '€6,240-9,360' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '€700-1,050', annual: '€8,400-12,600' },
  { category: 'Luxembourg CNS', monthly: '~5.6% of income', annual: 'Contribution-based' },
  { category: 'Luxembourg Supplementary', monthly: '€50-150', annual: '€600-1,800' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Luxembourg 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Luxembourg. Excellent healthcare, multilingual culture, high living standards, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Luxembourg"
  subheadline="Luxembourg offers exceptional healthcare, safety, and quality of life in a multilingual, cosmopolitan setting—though high costs match its high standards."
  heroImage="/images/countries/luxembourg-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Luxembourg</h2>
  <p>
    Luxembourg may be small but offers outsized quality of life—excellent healthcare, remarkable safety, multilingual culture, and central European location. It's one of the world's wealthiest countries with corresponding public services. The multilingual environment (French, German, Luxembourgish) suits cosmopolitan retirees.
  </p>

  <p>
    Luxembourg City provides modern infrastructure with historic charm. The Moselle valley offers wine country living. The Ardennes region has forests and villages. Despite small size, there's geographic variety—and Belgium, France, and Germany are all within easy reach.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Excellent; well-funded public system</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> French, German, Luxembourgish; English common</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> €3,000-5,000/month; high but manageable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Maritime; mild but cloudy</li>
      <li><strong>EU Status:</strong> EU founding member (Eurozone; uses EUR)</li>
      <li><strong>Size:</strong> 2,586 km²; entire country accessible</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Luxembourg's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Luxembourg has universal healthcare through CNS (Caisse Nationale de Santé). The system is well-funded and provides high-quality care. You typically pay upfront and receive 80-100% reimbursement. Most residents add supplementary insurance (mutuelle) to cover remaining costs.
  </p>

  <p>
    Hospitals include Centre Hospitalier de Luxembourg and Hôpitaux Robert Schuman. Quality is excellent with modern facilities. Wait times are minimal. Many doctors speak multiple languages including English. Cross-border care in Belgium, France, Germany is also accessible.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Upfront Payment System</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Luxembourg's system requires paying upfront, then claiming reimbursement (typically 80-100% depending on service). This is different from direct billing systems. You need funds available for payments, then submit claims. Supplementary insurance (mutuelle) covers remaining percentage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Luxembourg's immigration for non-EU retirees is restrictive:
  </p>

  <h3>Family Reunification</h3>
  <p>
    If you have Luxembourg citizen or resident family (spouse, children), family reunification is possible. Must demonstrate relationship and your sponsor's ability to support.
  </p>

  <h3>Sufficient Resources</h3>
  <p>
    Luxembourg allows residence for those with sufficient resources who won't burden social system. Requires proof of income/assets, accommodation, and health insurance. Process is case-by-case.
  </p>

  <h3>EU/EEA Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    Free movement applies. Register with commune after 90 days. Demonstrate sufficient resources and health coverage. Full access to CNS once registered and contributing.
  </p>

  <h3>No Formal Retirement Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Luxembourg doesn't have a specific retirement visa. Financial independence pathway exists but is not automatic—each case is evaluated.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Luxembourg:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residence application:</strong> Comprehensive health insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>EU citizens:</strong> EHIC initially; register for CNS</li>
    <li><strong>After residence:</strong> Access to CNS system with contributions</li>
    <li><strong>Supplementary:</strong> Mutuelle recommended for full coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Luxembourg</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is essential for residence applications. Once in CNS system, add local mutuelle for remaining co-pays. CNS reimburses 80-100% of approved rates. Keep international coverage for travel and treatment options in other countries if desired.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Luxembourg, these providers offer appropriate coverage:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Luxembourg</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong European network, accepted for residence</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Good Benelux region coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Luxembourg Mutuelle:</strong> DKV, Foyer for local supplementary</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage from providers that accept seniors for Luxembourg.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Luxembourg are high, reflecting expensive local healthcare:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Join CNS:</strong> Once eligible, public system is cost-effective</li>
    <li><strong>Local mutuelle:</strong> €50-100/month covers what CNS doesn't</li>
    <li><strong>Luxembourg exclusion:</strong> Once in local system, exclude from international</li>
    <li><strong>Cross-border care:</strong> Some treatments cheaper in neighboring countries</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Finance Professional, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Former banker, $5,000/month retirement income. Multilingual. Seeking quality life.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global for visa. Apply for financial independence residence. Join CNS when eligible.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Initially ~€520/month. After CNS: ~€280/month contribution + mutuelle ~€80 + Cigna (Lux excluded) ~€300.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Belgian EU Citizen, 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Moving from Brussels for quieter life. Belgian pension €2,200/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> EU rights apply. Register for CNS. Add mutuelle for full coverage. BUPA for Belgium visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> CNS + mutuelle ~€200/month + BUPA (Luxembourg excluded) ~€380/month.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: British with Luxembourg Spouse, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Post-Brexit, joining Luxembourg spouse. UK pension £2,500/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Family reunification visa. BUPA Global for application. Join CNS after residence. UK coverage included.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Initially ~€550/month. After CNS: ~€180/month + mutuelle + BUPA (Lux excluded) ~€350.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can non-EU retirees actually move to Luxembourg?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Possible but not straightforward. No formal retirement visa exists. You need: family connection, significant financial resources with demonstrated ability to support yourself, or other qualifying circumstances. Each case is evaluated individually. It's easier for EU citizens.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How expensive is Luxembourg really?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very expensive—among Europe's highest. Housing is particularly costly (Luxembourg City rivals Paris). Restaurants and services are pricey. However, salaries are high, and retirees with good income can live well. Public transport is free since 2020. Cross-border shopping in Germany helps.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What languages do I need?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Luxembourg is trilingual: French, German, Luxembourgish. French is most useful for daily life. German works in many contexts. Luxembourgish is national language but not essential for expats. English is widely spoken in international community. Many services available in English.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's the reimbursement system like?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Different from direct-billing systems. You pay provider, then submit claims to CNS for reimbursement (typically within 2 weeks). CNS reimburses 80-100% depending on service. Mutuelle covers the remainder. Need sufficient funds for upfront payments. System works well once understood.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that specialize in senior expat coverage for Luxembourg.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Luxembourg authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
